h6701.definition: from {{h6697}} and {{h7706}}; rock of (the) Almighty; Tsurishaddai, an Israelite; Zurishaddai.

h6702.definition: a primitive root; to blaze; burn.

h6703.definition: from {{h6705}}; dazzling, i.e. sunny, bright, (figuratively) evident; clear, dry, plainly, white.

h6704.definition: from an unused root meaning to glow; parched; dried up.

h6705.definition: a primitive root; to glare, i.e. be dazzling white; be whiter.

h6706.definition: from {{h6705}}; glaring, i.e. exposed to the bright sun; higher place, top.

h6707.definition: feminine of {{h6706}}; a parched region, i.e. the desert; dry land.

h6708.definition: from {{h6706}}; bare spot, i.e. in the glaring sun; higher place.

h6709.definition: from an unused root meaning to putrefy; stench; ill savour.

h6710.definition: from {{h6705}}; a dry place, i.e. desert; drought.

h6711.definition: a primitive root; to laugh outright (in merriment or scorn); by implication, to sport; laugh, mock, play, make sport.

h6712.definition: from {{h6711}}; laughter (in pleasure or derision); laugh(-ed to scorn).

h6713.definition: from an unused root meaning to dazzle; sheen, i.e. whiteness; white.

h6714.definition: from the same as {{h6713}}; whiteness; Tsochar, the name of a Hittite and of an Israelite; Zohar. Compare {{h3328}}.

h6715.definition: from the same as {{h6713}}; white; white.

h6716.definition: from {{h6680}}; a ship (as a fixture); ship.

h6717.definition: from the same as {{h6678}}; station; Tsiba, an Israelite; Ziba.

h6718.definition: from a form of {{h6679}} and meaning the same; the chase; also game (thus taken); × catcheth, food, × hunter, (that which he took in) hunting, venison, victuals.

h6719.definition: from the same as {{h6718}}; a huntsman; hunter.

h6720.definition: or צֵדָה; feminine of {{h6718}}; food; meat, provision, venison, victuals.

h6721.definition: or צִידֹן; from {{h6679}} in the sense of catching fish; fishery; Tsidon, the name of a son of Canaan, and of a place in Palestine; Sidon, Zidon.

h6722.definition: patrial from {{h6721}}; a Tsidonian or inhabitant of Tsidon; Sidonian, of Sidon, Zidonian.

h6723.definition: from an unused root meaning to parch; aridity; concretely, a desert; barren, drought, dry (land, place), solitary place, wilderness.

h6724.definition: from the same as {{h6723}}; a desert; dry place.

h6725.definition: from the same as {{h6723}} in the sense of conspicuousness (compare {{h5329}}); a monumental or guiding pillar; sign, title, waymark.

h6726.definition: the same (regularly) as {{h6725}}; Tsijon (as a permanent capital), a mountain of Jerusalem; Zion.

h6727.definition: or צִחָא; as if feminine of {{h6704}}; drought; Tsicha, the name of two Nethinim; Ziha.

h6728.definition: from the same as {{h6723}}; a desert-dweller, i.e. nomad or wild beast; wild beast of the desert, that dwell in (inhabiting) the wilderness.

h6729.definition: from an unused root meaning to confine; the pillory; stocks.

h6730.definition: from {{h6819}}; small; Tsior, a place in Palestine; Zior.

h6731.definition: or צִץ; from {{h6692}}; properly, glistening, i.e. a burnished plate; also a flower (as bright colored); a wing (as gleaming in the air); blossom, flower, plate, wing.

h6732.definition: the same as {{h6731}}; bloom; Tsits, a place in Palestine; Ziz.

h6734.definition: feminine of {{h6731}}; a floral or wing-like projection, i.e. a fore-lock of hair, a tassel; fringe, lock.

h6735.definition: from {{h6696}}; a hinge (as pressed in turning); also a throe (as a phys. or mental pressure); also a herald or errand-doer (as constrained by the principal); ambassador, hinge, messenger, pain, pang, sorrow. Compare {{h6736}}.

h6736.definition: the same as {{h6735}}; a form (of beauty; as if pressed out, i.e. carved); hence, an (idolatrous) image; beauty, idol.

h6737.definition: a denominative from {{h6735}} in the sense of ambassador; to make an errand, i.e. betake oneself; make as if...had been ambassador.

h6738.definition: from {{h6751}}; shade, whether literal or figurative; defence, shade(-ow).

h6739.definition: (Aramaic) probably corresponding to {{h6760}} in the sense of bowing; pray; pray.

h6740.definition: a primitive root; to roast; roast.

h6741.definition: feminine of {{h6738}}; Tsillah, an antediluvian woman; Zillah.

h6742.definition: from {{h6749}} in the sense of rolling; a (round or flattened) cake; cake.

h6743.definition: or צָלֵחַ; a primitive root; to push forward, in various senses (literal or figurative, transitive or intransitive); break out, come (mightily), go over, be good, be meet, be profitable, (cause to, effect, make to, send) prosper(-ity, -ous, -ously).

h6744.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h6743}}; to advance (transitive or intransitive); promote, prosper.

h6745.definition: from {{h6743}}; something protracted or flattened out, i.e. a platter; pan.

h6746.definition: from {{h6743}}; something prolonged or tall, i.e. a vial or salt-cellar; cruse.

h6747.definition: from {{h6743}}; something advanced or deep, i.e. a bowl; figuratively, the bosom; bosom, dish.

h6749.definition: a primitive root; properly, to tumble down, i.e. settle by a waving motion; sink. Compare {{h6750}}, {{h6751}}.

h6750.definition: a primitive root (identical with through the idea of vibration); to tinkle, i.e. rattle together (as the ears in reddening with shame, or the teeth in chattering with fear); quiver, tingle.

h6751.definition: a primitive root (identical with through the idea of hovering over (compare {{h6754}})); to shade, as twilight or an opaque object; begin to be dark, shadowing.

h6753.definition: from {{h6752}} and the active participle of {{h6437}}; shade-facing; Tselelponi, an Israelitess; Hazelelponi (including the article).

h6754.definition: from an unused root meaning to shade; a phantom, i.e. (figuratively) illusion, resemblance; hence, a representative figure, especially an idol; image, vain shew.

h6755.definition: (Aramaic) or צְלֶם; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h6754}}; an idolatrous figure; form, image.

h6756.definition: from {{h6754}}; shady; Tsalmon, the name of a place in Palestine and of an Israelite; Zalmon.

h6757.definition: from {{h6738}} and {{h4194}}; shade of death, i.e. the grave (figuratively, calamity); shadow of death.

h6758.definition: feminine of {{h6757}}; shadiness; Tsalmonah, a place in the Desert; Zalmonah.

h6759.definition: from {{h6738}} and {{h4513}}; shade has been denied; Tsalmunna, a Midianite; Zalmunna.

h6760.definition: a primitive root; probably to curve; used only as denominative from {{h6763}},; to limp (as if one-sided); halt.

h6761.definition: from {{h6760}}; a limping or full (figuratively); adversity, halt(-ing).

h6762.definition: the same as {{h6761}}; Tsela, a place in Palestine; Zelah.

h6763.definition: or (feminine) צַלְעָה; from {{h6760}}; a rib (as curved), literally (of the body) or figuratively (of a door, i.e. leaf); hence, a side, literally (of a person) or figuratively (of an object or the sky, i.e. quarter); architecturally, a (especially floor or ceiling) timber or plank (single or collective, i.e. a flooring); beam, board, chamber, corner, leaf, plank, rib, side (chamber).

h6764.definition: from an unused root of unknown meaning; Tsalaph, an Israelite; Zalaph.

h6765.definition: from the same as {{h6764}} and {{h259}}; Tselophchad, an Israelite; Zelophehad.

h6766.definition: from {{h6738}} and {{h6703}}; clear shade; Tseltsach, a place in Palestine; Zelzah.

h6767.definition: from {{h6750}} reduplicated; a clatter, i.e. (abstractly) whirring (of wings); (concretely) a cricket; also a harpoon (as rattling),a cymbal (as clanging); cymbal, locust, shadowing, spear.

h6768.definition: from an unused root meaning to split; fissure; Tselek, an Israelite; Zelek.

h6769.definition: from the feminine of {{h6738}}; shady; Tsillethai, the name of two Israelites; Zilthai.

h6770.definition: a primitive root; to thirst (literally or figuratively); (be a-, suffer) thirst(-y).

h6773.definition: feminine of {{h6772}}; thirst (figuratively, of libidinousnes); thirst.

h6774.definition: from {{h6771}}; a thirsty place, i.e. desert; drought, dry ground, thirsty land.

h6775.definition: a primitive root; to link, i.e. gird; figuratively, to serve, (mentally) contrive; fasten, frame, join (self).

h6776.definition: a yoke or team (i.e. pair); hence, an acre (i.e. day's task for a yoke of cattle to plough); acre, couple, × together, two (donkeys), yoke (of oxen).

h6777.definition: from an unused root meaning to fasten on; a veil; locks.

h6778.definition: from {{h6784}}; a cake of dried grapes; bunch (cluster) of raisins.

h6779.definition: a primitive root; to sprout (transitive or intransitive, literal or figurative); bear, bring forth, (cause to, make to) bud (forth), (cause to, make to) grow (again, up), (cause to) spring (forth, up).

h6780.definition: from {{h6779}}; a sprout (usually concrete), literal or figurative; branch, bud, that which (where) grew (upon), spring(-ing).

h6781.definition: or צָמִד; from {{h6775}}; a bracelet or arm-clasp; generally, a lid; bracelet, covering.

h6782.definition: from the same as {{h6777}}; a noose (as fastening); figuratively, destruction; robber.

h6783.definition: or צְמִתֻת; from {{h6789}}; excision, i.e. destruction; used only (adverbially) with prepositional prefix to extinction, i.e. perpetually; ever.

h6784.definition: a primitive root; to dry up; dry.

h6785.definition: from an unused root probably meaning to be shaggy; wool; wool(-len).

h6786.definition: patrial from an unused name of a place in Palestine; a Tsemarite or branch of the Canaanites; Zemarite.

h6787.definition: dual of {{h6785}}; double fleece; Tsemarajim, a place in Palestine; Zemaraim.

h6788.definition: from the same as {{h6785}}; fleeciness, i.e. foliage; highest branch, top.

h6789.definition: a primitive root; to extirpate (literally or figuratively); consume, cut off, destroy, vanish.

h6790.definition: from an unused root meaning to prick; a crag; Tsin, a part of the Desert; Zin.

h6791.definition: from an unused root meaning to be prickly; a thorn; hence, a cactus-hedge; thorn.

h6792.definition: or צֹנֶה; for {{h6629}}; a flock; sheep.

h6793.definition: feminine of {{h6791}}; a hook (as pointed); also a (large) shield (as if guarding by prickliness); also cold (as piercing); buckler, cold, hook, shield, target.

h6794.definition: from an unused root perhaps meaning to be hollow; a culvert; gutter, water-spout.

h6795.definition: a primitive root; to alight; (transitive) to cause to descend, i.e. drive down; fasten, light (from off).

h6796.definition: or צָנִן; from the same as {{h6791}}; a thorn; thorn.

h6797.definition: or צָנוֹף; or (feminine) צָנִיפָה; from {{h6801}}; a head-dress (i.e. piece of cloth wrapped around); diadem, hood, mitre.

h6798.definition: a primitive root; to blast or shrink; withered.

h6799.definition: probably for {{h6630}}; Tsenan, a place near Palestine; Zenan.

h6800.definition: a primitive root; to humiliate; humbly, lowly.
